2.7 Updated terminology: Incubate → Tickler + Someday/Maybe
===========================================================

The "Incubate" category has been split into two distinct types to better
align with GTD concepts:

   • *Tickler* - Items with a specific review date (formerly
     "Incubated").  Use this for time-based reminders and paused
     projects with a date to revisit.
   • *Someday/Maybe* - Items with no specific timeframe.  Use this for
     ideas and possibilities you might pursue eventually.

   This clarifies the distinction between "remind me on a specific date"
(Tickler) and "maybe someday with no commitment" (Someday/Maybe).

   Changes:
   • ‘org-gtd-incubate’ → ‘org-gtd-tickler’ (creates tickler items with
     timestamps)
   • New ‘org-gtd-someday’ command (creates someday items without
     timestamps)
   • New ‘org-gtd-reflect-someday-review’ command - Walk through someday
     items one-by-one with single-keystroke defer/clarify/quit actions.
     Optionally group items into named lists for focused reviews.  See
     *note Reviewing Someday/Maybe Items::.
   • Property value: ‘ORG_GTD: Incubated’ → ‘ORG_GTD: Tickler’ or
     ‘ORG_GTD: Someday’

   The old ‘org-gtd-incubate’ command still works as an alias to
‘org-gtd-tickler’ but is marked obsolete.


