4.4.3 The Effort Filter Explained
---------------------------------

The ‘effort’ filter works with your items' Effort property--the same one
org-mode uses for time estimates.

   The pattern is simple:

     (effort . (< "TIME"))    ;; less than TIME
     (effort . (> "TIME"))    ;; more than TIME
     (effort . (between "MIN" "MAX"))  ;; within range

   Time formats work how you'd expect:
   • ‘"15min"’ or ‘"0:15"’ → 15 minutes
   • ‘"1:30"’ or ‘"1h30min"’ → 1 hour 30 minutes
   • ‘"2:00"’ or ‘"2h"’ → 2 hours

   *The mental model:* Think of effort as "how big is this bite?"  Quick
wins are small bites.  Deep work is a full meal.


