4.4.5 The Priority Filter Explained
-----------------------------------

Priority in org-mode goes A (highest) → B → C (lowest).  The ‘priority’
filter matches this:

     (priority . A)           ;; exactly priority A
     (priority . (A B))       ;; priority A or B
     (priority . (>= B))      ;; B or higher (A and B)
     (priority . nil)         ;; no priority set

   *Important:* A is *highest* priority.  So ‘(>= B)’ means "B or
better"--which is A and B.

   *The mental model:* Priority answers "how important is this?"  Effort
answers "how long will it take?"  Together they help you match tasks to
your available time and energy.


