5.1 Your Daily Workflow
=======================

The GTD workflow has six steps.  You'll do the first four frequently
(even daily), and the last two periodically:

  1. *Capture* - Get things out of your head into your inbox
     (‘org-gtd-capture’)
  2. *Process* - Look at each inbox item one at a time
     (‘org-gtd-process-inbox’)
  3. *Clarify* - Edit the item to make it clear and actionable
  4. *Organize* - Categorize the item (‘org-gtd-organize’)
  5. *Engage* - Look at what you can do right now (‘org-gtd-engage’)
  6. *Review* - Periodically review your system for health

   You already practiced this in the *note Getting Started tutorials:
Getting Started with Org GTD. The sections below go deeper into each
part.

