5.4.15 Troubleshooting Projects with Graph View
-----------------------------------------------

   • Project is Stuck (has TODO tasks but no NEXT)

     Run ‘M-x org-gtd-reflect-stuck-projects’ to find stuck projects.

     Open the stuck project in graph view: ‘M-x
     org-gtd-show-project-graph’

     *What to look for*:
        • *No blue boxes?*  All tasks might be waiting for dependencies
          that are DONE.  Press ‘g’ to refresh.
        • *Orange boxes at layer 0?*  These should be blue (root tasks
          are never blocked).  Something's wrong with the dependency
          structure.
        • *Circular dependency?*  Org-gtd prevents these, but if you see
          arrows forming a loop, you've found a bug.

     *How to fix*:
        • Use graph view to understand the structure
        • Add a new root task (‘r’) if nothing can start
        • Refresh (‘g’) after any changes

   • Task Should Be NEXT But Shows as TODO

     In graph view, look at the task:
        • Is it orange (TODO)?
        • Trace arrows pointing TO it—these are its blockers
        • Are all those blockers blue?  Then something's wrong.
        • Are some blockers orange?  Then the task is correctly blocked.

     If blockers are actually DONE but still showing as blue, press ‘g’
     to refresh.

     *How to fix*: Use ‘B’ to modify blockers (uncheck incorrect ones),
     or use text command ‘org-gtd-task-clear-relationships’ to start
     fresh.

   • Too Many Tasks Are NEXT

     In graph view:
        • Count blue boxes
        • If you have 10+ blue tasks, you probably have dependency
          problems
        • Some tasks should depend on others but don't

     *How to fix*:
        • Select a task that should be blocked
        • Press ‘B’ to modify its blockers
        • Or use ‘s’ from an earlier task to add a successor that should
          come later

   • Graph Won't Open

     If ‘M-x org-gtd-show-project-graph’ doesn't work:

        • Verify you're on a project heading (not a task heading)
        • Check that the heading has ‘ORG_GTD’ property set to
          "Projects"
        • Try explicitly: ‘M-x org-gtd-show-project-graph’
        • Check for errors in ‘*Messages*’ buffer

   • Graph Shows No Tasks

     If the graph opens but shows no tasks:

        • Check if the project has subtasks (tasks should be subheadings
          under the project)
        • Verify tasks have ‘ORG_GTD_PROJECT_IDS’ property containing
          the project ID
        • Press ‘g’ to force a complete refresh
        • Check ‘*Messages*’ buffer for parsing errors

   • Task Shows Wrong State (NEXT vs TODO)

     If a task's color doesn't match its expected state:

        • Press ‘g’ to refresh (state might be stale from external
          edits)
        • Check the task's actual TODO state in the org file (press ‘e’
          to jump there)
        • Verify dependencies are correct (press ‘i’ to inspect
          relationships)
        • Look for completed tasks that haven't been refreshed

   • Can't Modify Dependencies

     If modification commands don't work:

        • Ensure a task is selected (should see highlighted box)
        • Press ‘?’ to verify commands are available in the transient
          menu
        • Check that you're in the graph view buffer, not the org file
          buffer
        • Try ‘g’ to refresh if the graph is in an inconsistent state


