6.2.4 Reviewing Someday/Maybe Items
-----------------------------------

Someday/maybe items are the graveyard of dreams—or the incubator of
future greatness.  The difference?  Regular review.  This feature helps
you stay connected to your possibilities without letting them become
forgotten fossils.

   *What is it*: A wizard-style workflow that shows you each someday
item one at a time, letting you quickly defer it (keep for later) or
clarify it (reactivate and make it actionable).

   *Who needs it*: Anyone with someday/maybe items who wants to
periodically review them during their GTD reflect process.

   • Your First Review in 60 Seconds

     Try this right now:

       1. Run ‘M-x org-gtd-reflect-someday-review’
       2. You'll see your first someday item in a read-only buffer
       3. Press ‘d’ to defer (keeps the item, logs that you reviewed it)
       4. Or press ‘c’ to clarify (reactivates the item)
       5. Press ‘q’ anytime to quit

     That's it.  You're reviewing your possibilities.

   • Understanding the Review Workflow

     When you see a someday item during review, you're asking yourself
     one question: "Is now the time to pursue this?"

          Someday item: "Learn to play piano"

          Is now the time?
            YES → Press 'c' (clarify) → Item becomes active, you organize it fresh
            NO  → Press 'd' (defer) → Item stays in someday, with timestamp logged

     *Why defer logs a timestamp*: The LOGBOOK entry creates a history.
     During future reviews, you can see how long items have been
     sitting.  An item deferred 50 times over 3 years might be ready to
     trash—or finally pursue.

   • Tutorial: Weekly Someday Review

     Here's how to incorporate this into your weekly review:

     *Basic flow*:
          M-x org-gtd-reflect-someday-review

          For each item:
          - Read it
          - Decide: defer or clarify?
          - Press d or c
          - Repeat until "Review complete"

     *What happens when you clarify*:
       1. The item's previous state is restored (if it was a delegated
          action, it remembers the delegate)
       2. You go through the organize flow
       3. After organizing, review automatically continues with the next
          item

     *What happens when you defer*:
       1. A "Reviewed [timestamp]" entry is added to the item's LOGBOOK
       2. Review advances to the next item
       3. The item stays in someday/maybe

   • Organizing Your Someday Items (Optional)

     If your someday list grows large, you can group items into named
     lists:

          ;; Optional: Define someday lists for focused reviews
          (setq org-gtd-someday-lists '("Work Ideas" "Personal Projects" "Learning" "Travel"))

     With this configured:

       1. *When organizing items as someday*: You'll be prompted to
          choose a list
       2. *When reviewing*: You'll be prompted which list to review (or
          "Unassigned")
       3. *Programmatic access*: Call ‘(org-gtd-reflect-someday-review
          "Work Ideas")’ directly

     This is entirely optional.  Without configuration, all someday
     items are reviewed together.

   • Common Patterns

     *Monthly Deep Review*:
          ;; Review everything, no list filter
          M-x org-gtd-reflect-someday-review

          ;; Go through each item thoughtfully
          ;; This might take 15-30 minutes for 50 items

     *Focused Category Review*:
          ;; With org-gtd-someday-lists configured:
          M-x org-gtd-reflect-someday-review → "Learning"

          ;; Only see learning-related someday items

     *Finding Stale Items*: Look at items during review that have many
     LOGBOOK entries spanning years.  Ask yourself: "Am I ever actually
     going to do this?"  If not, trash it.  If yes, this might be the
     time to clarify it.

   • Command Reference

     Key   Command   What it does
     ----------------------------------------------------------
     ‘d’   Defer     Log "Reviewed" entry, advance to next
     ‘c’   Clarify   Reactivate item, triggers organize flow
     ‘q’   Quit      End review, show statistics

     *Statistics*: When you quit or finish, you'll see: "Review
     complete.  X items reviewed, Y clarified."

   • ‘org-gtd-reflect-someday-review’

     *Arguments*: Optional LIST (string)

     *When to use*: During weekly/monthly reviews, or anytime you want
     to reconnect with your possibilities

     *What it does*:
        • If ‘org-gtd-someday-lists’ is configured: prompts for which
          list to review
        • Shows each someday item in a read-only buffer
        • Single-keystroke actions: ‘d’ (defer), ‘c’ (clarify), ‘q’
          (quit)
        • Tracks statistics (items reviewed, items clarified)

     *Configuration*:
          ;; Optional: Group someday items into lists
          (setq org-gtd-someday-lists '("Work Ideas" "Personal" "Learning"))

     *Example*:
          ;; Interactive (will prompt for list if configured)
          M-x org-gtd-reflect-someday-review

          ;; Programmatic (skip list prompt)
          (org-gtd-reflect-someday-review "Work Ideas")


