   • Updating Items Without Refiling

     **What this is:** A way to reconfigure existing GTD items (change
     their category, properties, or details) without moving them to a
     different location in your files.

     **Who needs it:** Anyone who wants to change how an item is
     organized while keeping it where it is - perfect for items already
     in projects, or when you like your current file organization.

     **Your first use (30 seconds):**

     You're looking at your agenda and see a single action that should
     actually be delegated.  But it's already in a specific project file
     and you want it to stay there:

       1. In agenda view, put point on the item
       2. Type: ‘C-u M-x org-gtd-clarify-agenda-item’
       3. Make your changes in the clarify buffer
       4. Type: ‘M-x org-gtd-organize’
       5. Type: ‘-n’ to toggle "Update in place (no refile)"
       6. Choose: ‘d’ for Delegate
       7. Fill in delegation details
       8. Done - item is updated but stays in its current location

     **How it works:**

     Normally when you organize an item, org-gtd moves (refiles) it to
     the appropriate GTD type location.  But sometimes you want to
     change the configuration without moving the item.

     There are two ways to trigger this:

     *Via prefix argument:*
        • ‘C-u M-x org-gtd-clarify-item’ - Clarify item at point without
          refiling
        • ‘C-u M-x org-gtd-clarify-agenda-item’ - Clarify agenda item
          without refiling

     *Via transient toggle:*
        • During organization, press ‘-n’ in the ‘org-gtd-organize’ menu
          to toggle "Update in place (no refile)"
        • The toggle is only available when NOT processing the inbox
          (inbox items must be refiled)

     When the skip-refile flag is set, organizing the item will:
        • Apply all the same configuration (properties, tags, hooks)
        • Update the item in its current location
        • NOT move it to a different file or heading

     **Common scenarios:**

     *Reconfiguring project tasks:*
        • Task is already in the right project file
        • You want to change it from single action to delegated
        • Use skip-refile to update without moving

     *Adjusting agenda items:*
        • Item appears in your daily agenda
        • You realize it needs different properties (change deadline,
          add delegation, etc.)
        • Use skip-refile to update configuration in place

     *Organizing items in custom locations:*
        • You've organized items in a specific way outside
          ‘org-gtd-directory’
        • You want to apply GTD types but preserve your file structure
        • Use skip-refile to maintain your organization

     **What stays the same vs what changes:**

     *Changes applied:*
        • GTD type (ORG_GTD property)
        • TODO keyword state
        • Properties (delegation info, dates, etc.)
        • Tags
        • All organize hooks

     *Preserved:*
        • File location
        • Position within file
        • Parent heading (for tasks in projects)
        • Sibling relationships

     **Technical details:**

     When you set the skip-refile flag (via ‘C-u’ prefix or ‘-n’
     toggle):
        • The flag is stored in the clarify buffer as
          ‘org-gtd-clarify--skip-refile’
        • Category finalize functions check this flag
        • If set, they call ‘org-gtd-organize--update-in-place’ instead
          of refiling
        • The original heading is replaced with the configured content
          from the WIP buffer
        • Archive categories (quick-action, knowledge, trash) always
          archive regardless of this flag

     **Migration note:**

     In previous versions, there was a special command
     ‘org-gtd-delegate-item-at-point’ for delegating items without
     moving them.  This command has been removed in favor of the more
     general skip-refile mechanism:

     *OLD way (no longer available):*
          M-x org-gtd-delegate-item-at-point

     *NEW way (version 4.0+):*
          ;; From agenda or file:
          C-u M-x org-gtd-clarify-item
          ;; or
          C-u M-x org-gtd-clarify-agenda-item
          ;; Then organize and press -n toggle
          M-x org-gtd-organize
          ;; Press -n to enable skip-refile
          ;; Choose delegation

     The new approach is more flexible - it works for ANY GTD type, not
     just delegation.


