6.3.1 Core GTD Properties
-------------------------

   • ORG_GTD

     *Used on*: All GTD items (projects, actions, calendar items,
     tickler items, etc.)

     *Purpose*: Identifies the type of GTD item

     *Values*:
     ‘"Projects"’
          Project heading
     ‘"Actions"’
          Project tasks and single actions
     ‘"Calendar"’
          Calendar items (appointments, deadlines)
     ‘"Tickler"’
          Items with specific review dates (time-based reminders)
     ‘"Someday"’
          Someday/maybe items (no specific timeframe)
     ‘"Delegated"’
          Delegated tasks (set in combination with DELEGATED_TO)

     *Example*:
          * My Project
          :PROPERTIES:
          :ORG_GTD: Projects
          :END:
          ** NEXT Task 1
          :PROPERTIES:
          :ORG_GTD: Actions
          :END:

     *Note*: This property is how org-gtd identifies items.  Don't
     modify manually unless you understand the implications.

   • ORG_GTD_REFILE

     *Used on*: Category headings that serve as refile targets

     *Purpose*: Marks a heading as a refile target for org-gtd's
     optional refile system (see *note Refiling section: Refiling to the
     appropriate area.)

     *Values*:
     ‘"Projects"’
          Target for refiling projects
     ‘"Actions"’
          Target for refiling single actions
     ‘"Calendar"’
          Target for refiling calendar items
     ‘"Tickler"’
          Target for refiling tickler items (time-based reminders)
     ‘"Someday"’
          Target for refiling someday/maybe items
     ‘"Habits"’
          Target for refiling habits

     *Multivalue support*: Values can be space-separated to accept
     multiple types.  For example, ‘Actions Projects’ makes a heading a
     valid target for both single actions and projects.

     *Example*:
          * Projects         <-- Can be at any level in any file
          :PROPERTIES:
          :ORG_GTD_REFILE: Projects
          :END:

          * Work/Development Projects   <-- Can have multiple targets per type
          :PROPERTIES:
          :ORG_GTD_REFILE: Projects
          :END:

          * Work Tasks      <-- Accepts multiple types
          :PROPERTIES:
          :ORG_GTD_REFILE: Actions Projects
          :END:

     *How it's set*:
        • Automatically created by ‘org-gtd-upgrade-v3-to-v4’ (renames
          ORG_GTD on level 1 headings)
        • Manually when creating custom refile targets
        • Via ‘org-entry-put’ in elisp: ‘(org-entry-put nil
          "ORG_GTD_REFILE" "Projects")’

     *Important notes*:
        • Org-gtd merges these targets with your ‘org-refile-targets’
          configuration
        • Can exist at ANY level in ANY file in ‘org-agenda-files’
        • You can have multiple refile targets for the same category
          type
        • A single heading can accept multiple types (space-separated
          values)
        • Your ‘org-refile-targets’ appear first, then ‘ORG_GTD_REFILE’
          targets


