6.4.3 Common Problems and Solutions
-----------------------------------

   • Project Shows No NEXT Tasks (Stuck Project)

     *Symptom*: Project has incomplete tasks but none are NEXT.

     *Diagnosis*:
        • Run ‘M-x org-gtd-show-project-graph’
        • Look for blue boxes (NEXT tasks)
        • If no blue boxes, check for:
             • Circular dependencies (arrows forming a loop)
             • All tasks waiting on incomplete tasks
             • Missing ORG_GTD_FIRST_TASKS property

     *Solution*:
        • Fix circular dependencies: Use ‘B’ to remove incorrect blocker
          relationships
        • Add root tasks: Use ‘r’ to create tasks that can start
          immediately
        • Run ‘org-gtd-validate-project-dependencies’ for detailed
          diagnosis

   • Too Many NEXT Tasks

     *Symptom*: Project shows 10+ blue boxes in graph view.

     *Diagnosis*: Tasks that should be dependent are independent.

     *Solution*:
        • In graph view, identify tasks that should depend on others
        • Select a task, use ‘B’ to add blockers it should wait for
        • Or use ‘s’ from an earlier task to add a successor that should
          come later

   • Task Won't Advance to NEXT

     *Symptom*: Completed a task, but dependent task still shows TODO
     (orange).

     *Diagnosis*:
        • In graph view, select the orange task
        • Press ‘i’ to show relationships
        • Check if all blockers are actually DONE

     *Solution*:
        • If blockers are DONE but showing as blocking: Press ‘g’ to
          refresh graph
        • If blocker shouldn't block this task: Use ‘B’ to modify
          blockers and uncheck it
        • If many wrong dependencies: Run
          ‘org-gtd-task-clear-relationships’, rebuild with ‘s~/~b’

   • Task States Inconsistent After External Edits

     *Symptom*: After editing on mobile app or resolving sync conflicts,
     task states don't match dependencies.

     *Examples*:
        • Tasks marked NEXT but blocked by incomplete dependencies
        • Tasks stuck in TODO when they should be NEXT
        • Multiple projects showing inconsistent states

     *Diagnosis*:
        • External tools (mobile apps, web interfaces) don't understand
          org-gtd dependency logic
        • Manual edits or sync conflicts disrupted task states
        • Affects all projects if you edited multiple files

     *Solution*:
        • For one project: Put point on project heading, run ‘M-x
          org-gtd-projects-fix-todo-keywords-for-project-at-point’
        • For all projects: Run ‘M-x
          org-gtd-projects-fix-all-todo-keywords’

     *Recommended workflow after mobile edits*:
       1. Sync files to Emacs
       2. Run ‘M-x org-gtd-projects-fix-all-todo-keywords’
       3. Verify with ‘M-x org-gtd-engage’ - should show correct NEXT
          tasks


