6.5.2 Understanding View Specs
------------------------------

A view spec is a simple list describing what you want to see:

     '((name . "View Name")     ;; What appears in the agenda header
       (type . delegated)       ;; Filter: show only delegated items
       (when . past))           ;; Filter: only items with past dates

   *Mental model:* Think of each line as a filter.  Items must pass ALL
filters to appear.  ‘(type . delegated)’ means "only delegated items".
Adding ‘(when . past)’ means "only delegated items whose check-in date
has passed".

   • Combining Filters

     Filters stack with AND logic:

          ;; Delegated items + past due = missed check-ins
          '((name . "Missed Check-ins")
            (type . delegated)
            (when . past))

          ;; Projects + specific area = focused view
          '((name . "Work Projects")
            (type . active-project)
            (area-of-focus . "Work"))

   • Multi-Block Views

     Show multiple filtered lists in one view:

          '((name . "My Dashboard")
            (blocks . (((name . "Calendar Today")
                        (type . calendar)
                        (when . today))
                       ((name . "Delegated Due")
                        (type . delegated)
                        (when . past))
                       ((name . "NEXT Actions")
                        (type . next-action)))))

     Each block is its own filter.  The view shows them stacked as
     separate sections.


